The American Academy of Pediatrics released its findings from a "cross-sectional study of 350 children aged 6 months to 4 years seen October to November 2014 at a pediatric clinic in an urban, low-income, minority community."

What it found MAY shock you:

"Most households had television (97%), tablets (83%), and smartphones (77%)."

"Three-fourths of 4-year-olds had their own mobile device. Half had their own television."

"Almost all children (96.6%) used mobile devices, and most started using before age 1."

"Parents gave children devices when doing house chores (70%), to keep them calm (65%), and at bedtime (29%)."
